value.value: The process in which the population of cells that make up a tissue undergo directed movement.
The process in which the population of cells that make up a mesenchyme undergo directed movement.
The process in which the population of cells that make up an epithelium undergo directed movement.

label.value: regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization by cell-cell adhesion

value.value: Any cell-cell adhesion process that modulates the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to membrane

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a membrane.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).

label.value: positive regulation of sphingolipid biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).

label.value: negative regulation of sphingolipid biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of sphingolipids within a cell.
The directed movement of substances from the Golgi to lysosomes.
The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization of an epithelial cell.
A cellular process that results in the breakdown of a Golgi apparatus that contributes to Golgi inheritance.
The reformation of the Golgi following its breakdown and partitioning contributing to Golgi inheritance.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of Golgi inheritance. Golgi inheritance is the partitioning of Golgi apparatus between daughter cells at cell division.

The process in which the structures of a chondrocyte are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a chondrocyte.
The joining of two lipid bilayers to form a single organelle membrane.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of kidney development. Kidney development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the kidney over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The kidney is an organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of kidney development. Kidney development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the kidney over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The kidney is an organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine.

Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of kidney development. Kidney development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the kidney over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The kidney is an organ that filters the blood and excretes the end products of body metabolism in the form of urine.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis, the process in which the branching structure of the ureteric bud is generated and organized. The ureteric bud is an epithelial tube that grows out from the metanephric duct. The bud elongates and branches to give rise to the ureter and kidney collecting tubules.

label.value: positive regulation of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis, the process in which the branching structure of the ureteric bud is generated and organized. The ureteric bud is an epithelial tube that grows out from the metanephric duct. The bud elongates and branches to give rise to the ureter and kidney collecting tubules.

label.value: negative regulation of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of branching involved in ureteric bud morphogenesis, the process in which the branching structure of the ureteric bud is generated and organized. The ureteric bud is an epithelial tube that grows out from the metanephric duct. The bud elongates and branches to give rise to the ureter and kidney collecting tubules.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of glomerulus development, the progression of the glomerulus over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The glomerulus is a capillary tuft surrounded by Bowman's capsule in nephrons of the vertebrate kidney.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of glomerulus development, the progression of the glomerulus over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The glomerulus is a capillary tuft surrounded by Bowman's capsule in nephrons of the vertebrate kidney.

Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of glomerulus development, the progression of the glomerulus over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The glomerulus is a capillary tuft surrounded by Bowman's capsule in nephrons of the vertebrate kidney.

The increase in size or mass of the spongiotrophoblast layer of the placenta where the increase in size or mass contributes to the progression of that layer over time from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: epithelium migration involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the population of cells that make up a wing epithelium undergo directed movement and contribute to imaginal disc-derived morphogenesis.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to imaginal disc-derived wing morphogenesis.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a muscle system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in a muscle system.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: positive regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label.value: negative regulation of peptide hormone secretion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: positive regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of calcium ion import

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the directed movement of calcium ions into a cell or organelle.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.
Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label.value: positive regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label.value: negative regulation of neural crest formation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.
Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.
Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleic acids.

definition.value: This term should not be used for direct annotation. It should be possible to make a more specific annotation to one of the children of this term.

label.value: positive regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: negative regulation of intracellular protein transport

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label.value: regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.
